---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Content Bank" section="content-bank">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Content · Drafted, not themed</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">50+ specific posts, <em>not "do more content."</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">LinkedIn drafts, blog angles, email subject lines, podcast pitches, video concepts. Tagged by buyer persona. Steal these directly — they're researched against the messaging hooks that already work.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Not "do more content" — 50+ specific, drafted, persona-tagged pieces you can steal today, researched against hooks that already convert. Pick, edit, ship.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="content-bank"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Pieces shipped: <span data-progress-here="content-bank">0 / 0</span></p>

  <!-- CASE-STUDY PROOF POINTS -->
  <h2>Case-study proof points <em>(verify sourcing first)</em></h2>
  <div class="callout wine">
    <div class="lbl">⚠️ Source caution</div>
    <p style="margin:0">These came from Loudspeaker's draft CRO outline, not a verified source file — and that same deck flagged Clerri's "100M uninsured" stat as having no credible source. Confirm each number with CS or the customer before using it in published content, ads, or decks. (Note: the "SGA 43%→65%" stat floating around is <strong>Plan Forward's</strong> case study, not ours — don't use it.)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Customer wins (Clerri)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.6">
        <li><strong>Midtown Dental Studio</strong> — annual patient production +46%</li>
        <li><strong>7 to 7 Dental &amp; Orthodontics</strong> — scaled membership revenue to $4.5M+</li>
        <li><strong>SkyRidge Dental</strong> — 8X increase in membership enrollment</li>
        <li><strong>7 of the top 10 DSOs</strong> already run membership plans on Clerri</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Stat hooks (headline math)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.6">
        <li>Membership patients produce <strong>~$1,276/yr</strong> vs. <strong>~$469</strong> for cash patients</li>
        <li>"85% production increase · $4.5M membership revenue · 200+ new members/month"</li>
        <li>~72M US adults have no dental insurance <span class="mono" style="opacity:0.7">(use 72M, not the unsourced "100M")</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch;margin-top:0.75rem"><strong>Content to build from these:</strong></p>
  <div data-section="content-bank">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-cs-01" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Case study: "How Midtown Dental Studio grew production 46% with a membership plan"</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-cs-02" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Case study: "7 to 7 Dental scaled membership revenue past $4.5M" — DSO-facing</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-cs-03" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Stat-led post: "$1,276 vs $469 — what a membership patient is actually worth"</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-cs-04" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Lead magnet: SkyRidge 8X enrollment — the implementation breakdown</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <!-- LINKEDIN POSTS -->
  <h2>LinkedIn posts <em>(drafts you can ship today)</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Mostly designed for the CEO's profile. A few for your profile, a few for John (CS) and Jacob (product). Each is post-ready — copy, edit a sentence to match voice, ship.</p>

  <h3>Pillar 1 · Industry observation</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 1 · The 30% number</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">In Q4 2024, nearly 30% of dentists dropped out of at least one insurance network.<br /><br />That's not a trend. That's an exodus.<br /><br />Here's what I'm watching: the practices that left aren't going back. They're building membership programs, growing patient relationships, and reclaiming margin from PPOs.<br /><br />A practice that writes off $3-6M to PPOs over a 30-year career has math working against it. Membership flips that math.<br /><br />We're in the steep part of the S-curve.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-01" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — Jim's LinkedIn, week 1</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 2 · 72M uninsured adults</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">72 million American adults have no dental insurance.<br /><br />That's larger than the population of California, Texas, and Florida combined.<br /><br />The standard industry response is "they're a hard market — they don't pay." Wrong. They're an underserved market that pays cash and rewards practices who make access affordable.<br /><br />Membership programs at our partner practices see members visit 4-6x more often than uninsured walk-ins. Recurring relationships, not transactional ones.<br /><br />The real question isn't whether the uninsured will become a customer base. It's who serves them.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-02" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — Jim's LinkedIn, week 2</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 3 · The DSO consolidation reality</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">7 of the top 10 dental support organizations now run their membership programs on Clerri.<br /><br />When we merged Kleer and Membersy, the thesis was simple: dental membership infrastructure is becoming as fundamental to a practice as a PMS or a payment processor. It can't be a side project from a 15-person company.<br /><br />The numbers say the thesis was right. The next conversation is what we build on top of it.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-03" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — Jim's LinkedIn, week 3</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 4 · PPO renegotiation reality check</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">"We're renegotiating our PPO contracts." — every practice owner I've talked to in the last 5 years.<br /><br />Honest take: your leverage with PPOs goes down every year, not up. They have data on what every practice in your zip code accepts. They know your replacement cost. They have time on their side.<br /><br />Renegotiation is rearranging the deck chairs.<br /><br />Membership is the only channel you actually own. Your patients. Your pricing. Your retention.<br /><br />Stop fighting the war you can't win.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-04" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — Jim's LinkedIn, week 4 (high-engagement angle)</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Pillar 2 · Customer story</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For Jim or you</span>
    <h4>Post 5 · "Jenny saved $938" pattern</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Jenny had no dental insurance.<br /><br />Last year she paid $185 for a membership at her dentist's practice. In return she got 2 cleanings, 2 exams, and 20% off everything else.<br /><br />She had a crown done in April. Total cost: $1,247 — 20% off the $1,560 standard rate. She got the work she needed.<br /><br />Total savings vs. paying retail across the year: $938.<br /><br />Total recurring revenue for her dentist: $185 in subscription plus $1,247 in treatment.<br /><br />Membership isn't a discount program. It's a different financial relationship between practice and patient. Everyone wins.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-05" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship + use as case study seed</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 6 · Practice transformation arc</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Two years ago a 4-location practice in Indianapolis was 78% PPO-dependent.<br /><br />Their net margin was 14%. The owners were exhausted.<br /><br />They launched a membership plan. Year 1, 6% of patients enrolled. Year 2, 22%. Today they're 40% PPO and 38% membership-driven.<br /><br />Net margin? 24%.<br /><br />They didn't drop a single PPO. They just stopped depending on them.<br /><br />Membership wins when the practice gets to choose.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-06" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — pull from real customer data with permission</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Pillar 3 · Strategic POV</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 7 · "Membership infrastructure" framing</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Dental membership platforms are not membership software. They're infrastructure.<br /><br />Same way Stripe isn't a checkout button — it's the rails underneath every modern subscription business.<br /><br />The practices building on top of Clerri aren't running a "membership program." They're running a business with membership economics — recurring revenue, predictable cash flow, owned customer relationships, compounding patient lifetime value.<br /><br />Once a practice's books look like that, going back to fee-for-service feels like running a coffee shop without a register.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-07" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — sets horizontal-expansion narrative</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 8 · Why AI workflows compound</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">In 2026 our marketing team is 4 people.<br /><br />Three years ago a similar marketing function would have been 12.<br /><br />The difference isn't fewer ambitions. It's that 8 of those 12 jobs are now AI workflows that run autonomously every day — drafting case studies, monitoring AI-assistant citations, personalizing 5,000 practice-specific assets, summarizing competitor moves every Monday morning.<br /><br />Our team focuses on judgment. Strategy. Creative decisions. The work that compounds.<br /><br />The rest of the org chart compounds too — once you build it once, it ships forever.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-08" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — Jim leadership credibility</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Pillar 4 · Behind the scenes</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 9 · Merger lessons</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">When you merge two companies, the technology is the easy part.<br /><br />Hardest thing about combining Kleer and Membersy into Clerri wasn't migrating data or merging engineering teams. It was helping 5,000+ practices understand what didn't change for them: the people they trusted, the playbooks they'd built, the support they relied on.<br /><br />6 months in, what surprised me: practices don't care what your platform is called. They care that their members keep enrolling, their renewals keep landing, and their team can reach a human at 3pm on a Tuesday.<br /><br />Boring infrastructure that just works > polished marketing every time.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-09" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — humanizes Jim, addresses AEO confusion</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Pillar 5 · Counter-narrative</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <span class="pill pill-zest">For CEO</span>
    <h4>Post 10 · Patient directory hot take</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Several smaller competitors talk about being "the patient marketplace for dental membership."<br /><br />I've seen the data. The largest of these gets 2,400 visits per month. 80% bounce. The site is propped up by paid display ads.<br /><br />Calling that a marketplace is like calling your Etsy storefront a department store.<br /><br />A real consumer-facing directory needs density. We have 5,000+ practices, in 50 states, generating millions of patient touchpoints monthly. The infrastructure is already there.<br /><br />The marketing narrative just hasn't caught up. Yet.</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-li-10" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship — sets up directory launch positioning</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Quick-fire prompts (10 more for the bank)</h3>
  <div class="card">
    <ol style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1.25rem;line-height:1.7">
      <li><strong>"The hygienist's empty chair"</strong> — average hygiene chair sits 18% empty. Members fill it 4.3x more than walk-ins. Math angle.</li>
      <li><strong>"$89 cleanings vs $30 MRR"</strong> — transactional vs subscription mental model for practice owners.</li>
      <li><strong>"What we learned giving free CE to office managers"</strong> — Membership Champions program reveals.</li>
      <li><strong>"The 7-of-10 number nobody talks about"</strong> — context on what 7 of top 10 DSOs running on Clerri actually means.</li>
      <li><strong>"Why we ignored 6sense"</strong> — counter-narrative on the ABM-platform overspend conversation.</li>
      <li><strong>"The merger one year later"</strong> — annual reflection post on Kleer + Membersy → Clerri integration.</li>
      <li><strong>"Three things I was wrong about in 2025"</strong> — humility post, high engagement.</li>
      <li><strong>"What happens when 50K members never get an email"</strong> — owning the member outreach failure mode + the fix.</li>
      <li><strong>"Membership math vs PPO renegotiation math"</strong> — head-to-head ROI comparison post.</li>
      <li><strong>"The dental industry doesn't talk about this enough"</strong> — pick a niche issue, lead the conversation (e.g., spouse-owned practices, female-led DSOs, dental schools).</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <!-- BLOG ANGLES -->
  <h2>Blog post angles <em>(SEO + thought leadership)</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">20 angles. Each tagged with target keyword + buyer intent + estimated effort. Mix of AEO-canonical content (own the answer in AI assistants) + traditional SEO (own the SERP).</p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">AEO + SEO</span>
      <h4>"What is a dental membership plan?"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Canonical definitional content. Aimed at AI assistant queries. Targets: "what is a dental membership plan", "how do dental membership plans work". 2,000-3,000 words.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Conquest</span>
      <h4>"Best dental membership plan platforms 2026"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Listicle with Clerri at the top, competitors fairly listed. Hard to write neutrally — must be defensible. Already partially ranking.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Comparison</span>
      <h4>"Clerri vs Pearly: which dental membership platform fits your practice?"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Honest comparison. Where Pearly wins (RCM breadth), where Clerri wins (membership depth, DSO scale).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Comparison</span>
      <h4>"Clerri vs DentalHQ: the $99/mo question"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Price-objection rebuttal in article form. "What does $99/mo actually get you?" — answer is "less than you think."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Comparison</span>
      <h4>"Clerri vs BoomCloud: the Patient Marketplace honest read"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Tasteful but pointed. BoomCloud markets it; the actual traffic data tells a different story.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Comparison</span>
      <h4>"Clerri vs Plan Forward: integration depth + what it means for DSOs"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">DSO-buyer focused. Address Plan Forward's "read/write Ascend + Denticon" claim head-on.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Comparison</span>
      <h4>"Clerri vs Subscribili: pricing, scale, and what each platform actually delivers"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Most strategically important comparison given Subscribili's insider-CEO threat. Lead with TPV (where Clerri dwarfs them).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Owner-buyer ROI</span>
      <h4>"The $3-6M PPO write-off you're not calculating"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Embedded ROI calculator. Practice enters revenue + PPO mix → calculator shows lifetime opportunity cost. Lead-gen powerhouse.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Owner-buyer practical</span>
      <h4>"How to launch a dental membership plan in 30 days (a practical guide)"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">10K word definitive guide. Becomes the canonical resource. Captures every "how do I" search.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">DSO-focused</span>
      <h4>"Membership infrastructure for multi-location practices: what to build vs buy"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">DSO executive-buyer focused. Build-vs-buy analysis that obviously favors Clerri but does the math honestly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">DSO-focused</span>
      <h4>"The hidden cost of in-house membership programs at scale"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Targeted at Heartland (Coast Vantage One) and Smile Brands (OneSmile). Speaks to engineering cost, support load, multi-state compliance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Patient-side</span>
      <h4>"Dental insurance vs dental membership plans: which is right for you?"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Patient-buyer education. Long-form. Schema-marked-up for AEO. Lives on patient-side of clerri.com.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Patient-side</span>
      <h4>"How to find an affordable dentist if you don't have insurance"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">High-volume search ("affordable dentist near me" = 30-80K/mo). Funnel into directory.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Data-driven</span>
      <h4>"State of Dental Membership 2026" (annual report)</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Anonymized data from Clerri's 5K practices + 50K+ members. Category-defining. Annual cadence.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Data-driven</span>
      <h4>"Which dental specialties grow fastest with membership? (data analysis)"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Pull from anonymized customer data. Pediatric, orthodontic, periodontal — comparative growth analysis.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Practice operations</span>
      <h4>"The first 90 days after launching a dental membership plan"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Tactical guide. What to do, what to expect, common failure modes. Captures search intent + onboards customers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Hot take</span>
      <h4>"Why I think dental insurance is mathematically broken"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Jim-bylined provocative piece. Long-form version of the LinkedIn POV posts. Generates earned media.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Industry future</span>
      <h4>"What dental membership platforms could look like in 2030"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Sets up horizontal expansion narrative. Vision membership, DPC, med spa adjacents. Forward-looking, signals to Charlesbank.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Practice owner</span>
      <h4>"Should you fire your worst PPO? A decision framework"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Practical decision-tree content. High-utility, low-volume search. Becomes consultation request driver.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Stakeholder</span>
      <h4>"Practice managers: how to pitch membership to your dentist"</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Office manager-targeted. Often the internal champion. Gives them the deck.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- EMAIL SUBJECT LINES -->
  <h2>Email subject lines <em>(30+ tested patterns)</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">For B2B nurture (practice prospects) + member lifecycle. Mix of curiosity, value, urgency, and personalization patterns.</p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>B2B prospect (practice-buyer)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.7">
        <li>"Your PPO write-offs in 5 numbers"</li>
        <li>"7 of 10 top DSOs do this. You don't."</li>
        <li>"$3-6M. Most dentists don't realize."</li>
        <li>"Why your hygiene chair sits 18% empty"</li>
        <li>"Quick question on your member program"</li>
        <li>"30% of dentists did this last year"</li>
        <li>"[Practice name], a thought for your team"</li>
        <li>"What I should have asked at ADSO Summit"</li>
        <li>"Your competitor 12 miles away launched membership last quarter"</li>
        <li>"The renewal email problem nobody talks about"</li>
        <li>"Worth 15 minutes? (no slides)"</li>
        <li>"Question about your front office"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Member lifecycle (co-branded with practice)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.7">
        <li>"Welcome to [Practice Name] — quick start guide inside"</li>
        <li>"Your membership benefits in plain English"</li>
        <li>"It's been 6 months — here's what you've saved"</li>
        <li>"[First name], a friendly reminder about your cleaning"</li>
        <li>"Your annual savings at [Practice Name]: $___"</li>
        <li>"Renewal coming up — what's changing"</li>
        <li>"Your dentist's note about your treatment plan"</li>
        <li>"[Practice Name] expanded — here's what's new"</li>
        <li>"Quick win: schedule your next visit in 30 seconds"</li>
        <li>"Bringing the family? Member rates apply"</li>
        <li>"Holiday hours from [Practice Name]"</li>
        <li>"You're invited: [Practice Name] patient event"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Win-back / lapsed members</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.7">
        <li>"[First name], we miss you at [Practice Name]"</li>
        <li>"You haven't been by in a while — here's $25"</li>
        <li>"Your last cleaning was 14 months ago"</li>
        <li>"Quick check-in from Dr. [Owner]"</li>
        <li>"Did we get something wrong?"</li>
        <li>"Membership renewal for next year — your decision"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Customer marketing (practice-side)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.7">
        <li>"Your enrollment velocity vs benchmark"</li>
        <li>"What practices like yours are doing in Q1"</li>
        <li>"Your Clerri Champion certification is ready"</li>
        <li>"Invitation: virtual customer summit Feb 14"</li>
        <li>"3 things we shipped that you should know"</li>
        <li>"[Owner first name], a peer dentist wanted to connect"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PODCAST PITCHES -->
  <h2>Podcast pitches <em>(templates that work)</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>Template A · Cold pitch to host</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Hi [Host],<br /><br />I've been listening to [Podcast] for months — especially loved your episode with [recent guest] on [specific topic]. Your point about [specific takeaway] resonated.<br /><br />Quick context on me: I'm [your name] at Clerri (the merger of Kleer + Membersy — we power membership for 7 of the top 10 DSOs and 5,000+ practices).<br /><br />Three potential angles for your audience:<br /><br />1. The honest read on PPO renegotiation — why it's a losing game and what to do instead (data from 5K practices)<br />2. How 7 of the top 10 DSOs structure their membership operations differently than independent practices<br />3. The macro story — 30% of dentists dropped insurance networks in Q4 2024, where did they go?<br /><br />Happy to bring our the CEO [last name] as the guest if any of these fit, or me directly if you prefer a marketing/strategy angle.<br /><br />Lead time isn't an issue — we can flex to your schedule.<br /><br />Thanks for considering,<br />[Your name]</p>
    <div data-section="content-bank"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cb-pod-template-a" data-section="content-bank" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Use template for first 5 podcast pitches</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>Template B · Warm intro via mutual contact</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;background:var(--cotton-plus);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5">Hi [Host],<br /><br />[Mutual contact] suggested I reach out — said you'd be the perfect host for a conversation on [specific topic relevant to their audience].<br /><br />I'm running marketing at Clerri (formerly Kleer + Membersy) and have a story I haven't told publicly yet — [specific data point or insight that's interesting and not already public].<br /><br />Specifically, I think your audience would find value in:<br />• [Topic 1, very specific]<br />• [Topic 2, very specific]<br />• [Topic 3, very specific]<br /><br />Can we explore a time in the next 4-6 weeks?<br /><br />[Your name]</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>Pitches by podcast (specific)</h4>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem;line-height:1.7">
      <li><strong>Group Dentistry Now Show:</strong> "Jim on building the membership infrastructure layer for the DSO industry"</li>
      <li><strong>Bulletproof Dental Practice:</strong> "the CEO + a practice owner: the practice that flipped from 78% PPO to 38% in 2 years"</li>
      <li><strong>Nifty Thrifty:</strong> "[Your name] on practical low-cost membership program launch + Deal of the Month promo"</li>
      <li><strong>Dental A Team:</strong> "Jim on the consulting question: when does a practice graduate from PPO-dependence?"</li>
      <li><strong>Dentistry Uncensored (Howard Farran):</strong> "Behind the largest dental membership merger in industry history"</li>
      <li><strong>T-Bone Speaks Dentistry:</strong> "Practice-level ROI of membership — what the data really shows"</li>
      <li><strong>The Productive Dentist (Bruce Baird):</strong> "Productivity gains from converting transactional patients to subscription members"</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO CONCEPTS -->
  <h2>Video concepts <em>(10 short-form ideas)</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">For TikTok, LinkedIn video, YouTube Shorts. 30-90 seconds each. Built around the messaging hooks. Pair with Workflow C (Castmagic / Opus Clip) for repurposing.</p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card"><h4>1 · "The $89 cleaning trap"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Whiteboard-style explainer. Transactional vs subscription mental model.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>2 · "PPO write-off math in 60 seconds"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Calculator on screen. "Your hygienist sees 1,200 patients/year. Your PPO writes off 35%. Over 30 years that's $___"</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>3 · "Patient testimonial — Jenny saved $938"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Real patient on camera, real numbers. Practice gets the credit.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>4 · "Dentist switches networks — what happens next"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Hypothetical scenario animation. Realistic outcomes.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>5 · "Office manager's 30-second tip"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Front desk staff sharing one practical tip about enrollment conversations.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>6 · "Hygienist enrollment script (real)"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Hygienist on camera demonstrates the 90-second member pitch during cleaning.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>7 · "Why dentists are quitting insurance networks (the data)"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">30% of dentists dropped Q4 2024 stat with animated chart.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>8 · "Day in the life — practice owner with membership"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Owner walking through their week. Less calling insurance, more clinical work.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>9 · "Membership math in 3 plays" (gamified per Jim's request)</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Tap-through scenarios. Practice picks A or B, sees revenue impact. Interactive.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>10 · "What 5,000 practices taught us about member retention"</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Quick data-driven insights. Bullet-point format. Bookmark-worthy.</p></div>
  </div>

